comment._content:
Boeing YC-97J Stratofreighters 52-2762 (near), and 52-2693 (far), two ex KC-97G-28-BOs modified as flying test beds for Pratt and Whitney YT34-P-5 turboprops. The first flight of this model was in February 1955. Both were later acquired by Aero Spacelines and parts used for B-377SG 'Super Guppy' N1038V, a registration of what was originally a Pan Am Stratocruiser. The Super Guppy is now preserved at the Pima Air and Space Museum in Tucson, AZ.

Below is 52-2693.
